stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: CryptoDefense Malware Analysis from Third Party Submissions
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
The malicious files analyzed are related to the CryptoDefense malware. The files call back to a total of 23 command and control domains.
This report is based on US-CERT MIFR-377262.

stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
Type PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows
Antivirus Kaspersky Trojan-Ransom.Win32.Cryptodef.hh McAfee RDN/Ransom!eg Microsoft Trojan:Win32/Malagent!gmb Symantec WS.Reputation.1 TrendMicro TROJ_GEN.R0CBC0DES14
Upon execution, this file renames itself and creates copies, with the same MD5 hash, in various locations on the victim machine. In the test environment, those locations were:
C:\<Random_String>\<Random_String>.exe %AppData%\ <Random_String>.exe %USERPROFILE%\Start Menu\Programs\Startup\<Random_String>.exe
